                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.09181/2604.09181v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Method overview.We propose training rectified flows with mixed source distributions, obtained by interpolating a conditional and a simple unconditional distribution. The conditional distribution is predicted from a signalκ\\kappa, which is possibly informative, e.g. a specific data example, a class label, or entirely independent, e.g. random noise. The learned conditional distribution provides a trajectory structure that minimizes the degree of intersections, which is inherited by the mapping from the unconditional source distribution.",
